{
  "stem": "19690.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 60.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He would play the piano and his son would help on the drums to try and get my ear to hear what they wanted me to sing because I am relatively tone deaf.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I studied there regularly, went there every week when I didn't have school on Wednesday afternoon, and then went there also on Shabbat afternoon to study with this rabbi to get ready for my bar mitzvah.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Also, when we got to Marseille, the most urgent priority was learning French because we could not go around Marseille saying we were German because [INAUDIBLE] were hated and we had to say that we were from Alsace-Lorraine, that we were refugees from Alsace-Lorraine.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But you can't be from Alsace-Lorraine and not know French.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So the committee hired a man to kill his from Alsace-Lorraine spoke no German, and we had sessions five days a week with him learning French, the written French and spoken French.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And it was an interesting experience learning from somebody who could not translate for you.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And we would act out these different words or bring samples, anything to get him to understand what we were saying.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Not only that, but we had dictionaries that we used because we had to have him understand.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And as we were learning French, he was learning German.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And by September of 1941, we were fluent enough that I was able to go to a public school.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And I attended the school near the hotel, which was the boys' school near the cathedral up on the hill in the Harbor District.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I had a very understanding teacher who knew what the situation was.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And the French theory of learning is memorizing.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "I was a lousy memorizer, much less in a foreign language, so he was very lenient with that.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
